<dl id="n36012c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36012c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36012c"> 12(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mori / drain / Aymery</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The northern wall, famous in the siege of Delhi in 1857, extends three-quarters of a mile from the Water bastion to the Shah, commonly known as the <mark>Mori <font color="green">[or drain gate]</font></mark>, bastion; the length of the west wall from this bastion to the <mark>Ajmere gate</mark> is 1&frac14;m. <small> &ldquo;DELHI&rdquo; <a name="EBDH" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDH"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 954b</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
